issue.body:
Hi,

With version 6.2.1 we are starting to receive these errors

```
Message of type AutoMapper.AutoMapperMappingException occurred: 
Error mapping types.

Mapping types:
Bouwstof -> Bouwstof
Pim.Models.Bouwstoffen.Bouwstof -> Pim.Repositories.EF.Bouwstof

Type Map configuration:
Bouwstof -> Bouwstof
Pim.Models.Bouwstoffen.Bouwstof -> Pim.Repositories.EF.Bouwstof

Property:
BouwstofSpecificaties
- Unable to cast object of type 'System.Collections.Generic.HashSet`1[Pim.Repositories.EF.BouwstofSpecificatie]' to type 'System.Collections.Generic.List`1[Pim.Repositories.EF.BouwstofSpecificatie]'.

   at lambda_method(Closure , Bouwstof , Bouwstof , ResolutionContext )
   at Pim.BouwstofServices.BouwstofService.<UpdateCurrentVersionInstance>d__156.MoveNext() in C:\Git\PIM\Pim.Solution
```

We are using a Service Fabric Stateless service, where in the class the mapper configuration is created:

```
/// <summary>
        /// The mapper
        /// </summary>
        private IMapper mapper;

        /// <summary>
        /// Gets a new instance of the mapper.
        /// </summary>
        private IMapper MapperInstance
        {
            get
            {
                if (mapper == null)
                {
                    MapperConfiguration config = new MapperConfiguration(cfg =>
                    {
                        cfg.AddProfile(new Repositories.MappingProfile(TenantName));
                        cfg.AddProfile(new AzureSearch.MappingProfile());
                        cfg.AddProfile(new MappingProfile(TenantName));
                    });

                    mapper = config.CreateMapper();
                }

                return mapper;
            }
        }
```

The mapping is created like this:
```
CreateMap<Models.Bouwstoffen.Bouwstof, Repositories.EF.Bouwstof>()
                .ForMember(d => d.BouwstofId, opt => opt.MapFrom(src => src.Id))
                .ForMember(d => d.BouwstofSoort, opt => opt.Ignore())
CreateMap<Models.Bouwstoffen.BouwstofSpecificatie, EF.BouwstofSpecificatie>()
                .ForMember(d => d.BouwstofSpecificatieId, opt => opt.MapFrom(src => src.Id))
                .ForMember(d => d.Documents, opt => opt.Ignore());
```

And then in our method we call

```
// apply the changes to the original entity (update)
bouwstofEntity = MapperInstance.Map(newBouwstof, bouwstofEntity);
```

This used to work, but is not working anymore...  What are we doing wrong? This used to work without any problem on 6.1.1 and earlier...
